comment: [Observable in enhanced video] Irving (CLE) moves his pivot foot. Because of the defensive pressure by Williams (DAL), the official is watching the defender to look for any illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
RHH shows Williams (DAL) makes contact with the ball and causes Irving (CLE) to lose control of it, which allows him to dribble again.
LHH shows that Williams (DAL) cleanly strips the ball from Irving (CLE).
Irving (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Williams' (DAL) post-up.
Pachulia (DAL) grabs and holds Love (CLE), affecting his ability to defend.
Smith (CLE) makes incidental contact with Matthews (DAL) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with Matthews' (DAL) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Williams (DAL) jumps from point A to point B into James (CLE) and makes contact to the body that affects his jump shot attempt.

Parsons (DAL) hand checks James (CLE) and affects his RSBQ. The illegal contact occurs prior to the gather by James and a non-shooting foul is correctly called. Since Dallas was in the penalty James was awarded 2 free throws.
RHH shows that Thompson (CLE) makes incidental contact with Williams (DAL) that does not affect his RSBQ or shot attempt.
Harris (DAL) turns after jumping and makes body to body contact with James (CLE) during his dunk attempt.
Parsons (DAL) sets the screen on Shumpert (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Shumpert (CLE) and Nowitzki (DAL) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Shumpert (CLE) makes contact with Nowitzki (DAL) with a stayed forearm above the free throw line extended.
Shumpert (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Nowitzki (DAL).
Love (CLE) sets the screen on Williams (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
McGee (DAL) sets the screen on Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
James (CLE) makes incidental contact with Nowitzki (DAL) while attempting to deflect the entry pass.
James (CLE) obtains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Williams (DAL).
Love (CLE) and McGee (DAL) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Love (CLE) sets the screen on Williams (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dellavedova (CLE) clamps Matthews' (DAL) arm and affects his ability to establish position in the post.
Dellavedova (CLE) does not obtain a legal guarding position and makes contact with Williams' (DAL) body that affects his driving layup attempt.

[Observable in enhanced video] Matthews (DAL) moves his pivot foot. Because of the defensive pressure during the double team by Shumpert (CLE) and Love (CLE), officials are watching the defenders to look for any illegal contact and do not pick up the pivot foot.
As Williams (DAL) attempts to get over the screen, he makes contact with Irving (CLE) that affects his RSBQ.
Parsons (DAL) and Shumpert (CLE) make incidental contact with one another during a switch on a screen.

James (CLE) makes contact with the backboard while attempting to block Williams' (DAL) driving layup attempt, however the contact with the backboard does not cause an unnatural bounce of the ball and affect the layup attempt.
Williams (DAL) and Shumpert (CLE) make incidental contact with one another away from the ball.
Harris (DAL) sets the screen on James (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Williams (DAL) maintains contact with the floor during his pump fake.
RHH shows that James (CLE) legally contests Nowitzki's (DAL) layup attempt.
Parsons (DAL) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) drive to the basket. Any contact on the play is initiated by James.
Parsons (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds. LHH shows that he does not fully clear the lane on his first attempt to clear.
James (CLE) does not go through Williams' (DAL) space during his spin move.
Correctly called OOB last touched by Shumpert (CLE). Dallas retained possession.
Shumpert (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Williams (DAL). Any contact on the play is initiated by Williams.
Harris (DAL) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Williams (DAL) released the ball prior to the clock expiring was confirmed.
